<article>
    <h1>BAK&#xAD;ERY GEM IN THE HEART&#xAD;LAND</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200724/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-07-24"><time>2020-07-24</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>With over 100 va­ri­eties of breads and cakes avail­able daily, you are spoilt for choice the mo­ment you en­ter this bak­ery in Hougang.</p>
    <p>The lat­est ad­di­tions are Cho­co­late Mexico Bun ($1.50) and New Cho­co­late Bun ($1.50), both made us­ing the same cho­co­late fill­ing. The dif­fer­ence is that the Cho­co­late Mexico Bun has colour­ful swirls on its ex­te­rior.</p>
    <p>The breads sold here are in­cred­i­bly soft and fluffy.</p>
    <p>The Ja­panese Red Bean Bun ($1.50) is gen­er­ously filled with Ja­panese azuki bean paste and the Taro Bun ($1.50) is packed with so much yam, it is like a bun ver­sion of orh nee, the Teochew yam paste dessert.</p>
    <p>The 3.5-inch Cheese Cake ($4), which is sold chilled, is cot­tony soft and tastes just as fresh two days later.</p>
    <p>If you like chif­fon cakes, go for the Hand Torn Cheese Chif­fon Cake ($4.50), which is baked and sold in a dis­pos­able chif­fon cake mould. At first bite, you can taste the sweet, savoury rich­ness of eggs and milk. It is best to tear pieces of the cake and eat it as you would with cot­ton candy.</p>
    <p>I tried both the stan­dard 8-inch Pan­dan Chif­fon Cake ($6) and Hand Torn Pan­dan Chif­fon Cake ($3.80), and rec­om­mend the lat­ter. The fra­grance and flavour of the pan­dan and co­conut milk are more in­tense in the Hand Torn ver­sion and its tex­ture is lighter and fluffier.</p>
    <p>Tart lovers should go for the Blue­berry Cheese Tart ($1.50) and Co­conut Tart ($1.30). The sweet pas­try tart shells are made in-house and the blue­berry tart is packed with plenty of cream cheese.</p>
    <p>WHERE: 259 Bak­ery, 01-259 Block 644 Hougang Av­enue 8 MRT: Hougang</p>
    <p>OPEN: 6am to 9.30pm daily</p>
    <p>TEL: 6385-3819</p>

